name: Psychoactivevision - caustic [KOS-tik]
description: The first release utilising Space Cyclops as a Distro. With every physical album you get a link to the free remix album. Psychoactivevision are an avant-garde noise band, and are currently working on a new album. These albums are quickly running out, so order fast.

name: Gut Milk - Exploding Head Syndrome (Special 32 bit edition Floppy Disk)
description:
Gut Milk started as a no-wave band in 2009, and have evolved into an experimental music group focusing on making intense music with even more intense live shows. They are currently working on their first EP, out through Blast Drone Records.

This is a special, limited run edition of their first single Exploding Head Syndrome, its a degraded 32 bit edition and comes on coloured floppy disks. It has been released through Blast Drone Records.

name: Hisoka Mitsuyo - Prelude in 3 Parts (OSAKA HELLO VOICE MINE, Gold Coins to a Cat, Gold Cats to the s
description: A 3 floppy disk set, of the opening noise works by japanese noise artist, Hisoka Mitsuyo. Disk 1, OSAKA HELLO VOICE  MINE is a 20 minute ambient noise track, which is in heavy contrast to all other works by Hisoka. Disk 2, Gold Coins to a Cat, is a 7 minute noise masterpiece, and Disk 3 is a short, but ear destroying noise piece which no body dares to listen to. All the of these floppy disks come for a very small price and will no doubt run out fast.
